"Whoopsie" is the name given to several unobtainable items in the cache. Many items were changed to have their noted forms removed: since items could not be fully removed once created, Whoopsies were added in a hidden update to fill these slots. The actual item was just a copy of a pink skirt.

In RuneScape, the item later became viewable via Quick Chat, causing much confusion.

All of the Whoopsies were gradually removed from Old School RuneScape and replaced; however, one remains, which was originally the noted form of the "Chompy bird object" item that appears in the chatbox when checking the Chompy bird kill count.

Changes[edit | edit source]

Date Changes
10 December 2014
(update)
  • The item was renamed from "Whoopsie" to "Null".
  • The examine was changed from "Just chuck this away, it's useless!" to "null".
  • The "Wear" option was removed.

List of whoopsies[edit | edit source]

Originally, there were 191 separate whoopsies in Old School RuneScape, which are listed here. Of these, only one remains.
